 M"]', 0, 'First letter codes the outer shape (B = square, C = circle, A = triangle); Second letter codes the shading (Z = white, X = grey, Y = black); Third letter codes the size (G = large, F = small); Fourth letter codes the inner mark (L = cross, K = ring, M = diamond). The final figure''s code is B Y F M.', false),
  (113, 3, 'Which cube can be made from this net?
